# Brand & Themes (Visionary)

Source of truth: `docs/design.md` — Functional Color Rules, Iridescence Rules, Theme Architecture, Product Themes.

## Color Purpose

Every color must communicate meaning. No decorative-only color in product UI.

- **Green** — luck, nature, growth (`brand.default`, `action.primary*`)
- **Lavender** — magic, emotion, imagination (default accent)
- **Status palettes** — success, warning, error, info for feedback only

Brand colors are not status colors. Status colors are not brand accents.

## Iridescence

Iridescence is **decorative only**. Allowed: hero, celebrations, premium highlights, marketing surfaces, storytelling, decorative dividers.

**Never** use iridescence for: status states, body text, core actions, errors, warnings.

Hero CTA gradients/iridescent treatments are **marketing exceptions** — do not promote to semantic tokens.

## Theme Architecture

```
Foundation → Semantic → Component → Theme → Product UI
```

- Load **one theme** per product surface (Lucky Charm, Dream Fund, etc.)
- Themes **remap existing slots** only — no new primitive scales or component keys
- Theme overrides resolve before render; document every override in the theme definition

### Themes may override

`brand.*`, `action.accent*`, `action.primary*` (with caution), decorative highlight refs

### Themes must NOT override

`status.*`, `disabled.*`, `focus.*`, `overlay.*`, functional color scales

## Accent vs Status (Dream Fund)

When accent maps to warning palette (Dream Fund):

- Accent → secondary buttons, branding, highlights
- Alerts/validation → always `status.warning.*` / `status.error.*`
- **Never** wire theme accent into alert or input error slots

## Do Not

- Hardcode brand hex values in product UI
- Create product-specific tokens in foundations
- Use theme accent colors on status surfaces
- Fork `docs/design.md` for new products — add a theme file instead
